  "business_context": "Affiliation records solve a common nonprofit modeling problem: a single individual is often associated with multiple organizations simultaneously. They might be a Contact whose primary Account is their Household, while also being a board member at a foundation, a senior executive at a corporate partner, an alumnus of an affiliated school, and a former employee of a current major-gift donor. Each of these is a meaningful relationship that drives different cultivation strategies, but Salesforce's standard one-to-one Account-to-Contact model can only hold one. Affiliation records add a many-to-many junction. Modeling varies: NPSP has Affiliation as a custom object (npe5__Affiliation__c) with start/end dates, role, status, and primary-flag; CiviCRM uses Relationship records (with relationship_type_id values like Employee Of, Board Member Of, Volunteer For); Bloomerang has Relationships with similar role types. The B2B systems handle this poorly — Salesforce vanilla has AccountContactRelation but it's underused; HubSpot's primary-and-secondary company associations help but aren't role-aware. When interviewing clients, surface \"Affiliation\" by asking how they track contacts who have multiple meaningful organizational connections, and whether those connections need start/end dates and role classifications.",
  "catalog_id": "affiliation",
